    <bioghist>Family of Stephen F. Brown, Michigan Republican state senator of Schoolcraft Township, Kalamazoo County, Michigan, and his son Frank M. Brown, who served with Co. L, Fifth Michigan Cavalry, during the Civil War.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Correspondence relating to the Mexican War, national politics, family affairs, and Frank M. Brown's service with the Fifth Michigan Cavalry during the Civil War; also receipts and indentures; and an address to the second annual meeting of the Michigan State Grange. Correspondents include: Zachariah Chandler, Henry H. Crapo, and W. C. Edsell.</scopecontent>
